<item>
            <title>[TINKERPOP-2095] GroupStep looks for irrelevant barrier steps</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TINKERPOP-2095</link>
                <project id="12316520" key="TINKERPOP">TinkerPop</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;GroupStep&lt;/tt&gt; looks for a &lt;tt&gt;Barrier&lt;/tt&gt; step to determine the reducing bi-operator. This is wrong and I&apos;m really surprised that this has never been spotted before.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;gremlin&amp;gt; g.V().hasLabel(&apos;person&apos;).as(&apos;p&apos;).out(&apos;created&apos;).group().by(&apos;name&apos;).by(select(&apos;p&apos;).values(&apos;age&apos;).sum())
java.lang.Long cannot be cast to org.apache.tinkerpop.gremlin.process.traversal.traverser.util.TraverserSet
Type &apos;:help&apos; or &apos;:h&apos; for help.
Display stack trace? [yN]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the query above the first barrier step is a &lt;tt&gt;NoOpBarrier&lt;/tt&gt; step (added by &lt;tt&gt;PathRetractionStrategy&lt;/tt&gt;). This step obviously has no reducing bi-operator. What we really want to do is look for the first barrier step that is not a &lt;tt&gt;LocalBarrier&lt;/tt&gt; step.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
